# Phase 1 – Project Planning & Requirement Analysis

## Project Title
Mise en Place – AI Recipe Studio

## Introduction
Mise en Place is an AI-powered recipe generation platform that helps users create recipes using ingredients available at home.

## Problem Statement
Many users have ingredients but struggle to decide what meal they can prepare. Existing recipe platforms require manual searching and do not provide personalized suggestions.

## Objectives

- Generate recipes using AI
- Reduce food waste
- Provide personalized cooking suggestions
- Support dietary preferences
- Improve cooking convenience

## Scope

The system allows users to:

- Enter ingredients
- Select cuisine preferences
- Choose dietary restrictions
- Set serving size
- Generate recipes instantly

## Functional Requirements

- User ingredient input
- Cuisine selection
- Diet selection
- Recipe generation
- Nutrition information
- Print recipe
- Copy recipe

## Non-Functional Requirements

- Fast performance
- User-friendly interface
- Responsive design
- Cross-browser support

## Expected Outcome

An intelligent recipe assistant capable of generating professional-quality recipes instantly.

# Phase 2 – System Design & Architecture

## Technology Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|----------|
| HTML5 | Structure |
| Tailwind CSS | Styling |
| JavaScript | Logic |
| Groq API | AI Integration |

## System Architecture

User Input
↓
Prompt Builder
↓
Groq AI API
↓
JSON Parser
↓
Recipe Renderer
↓
Recipe Output

## Modules

### User Input Module
Collects ingredients and preferences.

### Prompt Builder Module
Builds structured prompts for AI.

### AI Integration Module
Communicates with Groq API.

### Parser Module
Converts JSON response into usable data.

### Recipe Display Module
Shows generated recipes.

## User Interface Design

- Ingredient Form
- Cuisine Selection
- Diet Selection
- Recipe Card
- Nutrition Panel

## Workflow

1. User enters ingredients
2. Prompt is generated
3. Request sent to AI
4. AI returns recipe
5. Recipe displayed

# Phase 3 – Development & Implementation

## Features Implemented

### Ingredient-Based Recipe Generation
Generates recipes from available ingredients.

### Cuisine Selection
Supports multiple cuisine styles.

### Dietary Restrictions
Supports Vegan, Vegetarian, Keto and more.

### Servings Adjustment
Recipe quantities adapt to selected servings.

### Time Constraints
Recipes generated within cooking time limits.

### Regenerate Feature
Creates alternative recipes.

### Copy Recipe Feature
Copies recipe to clipboard.

### Print Recipe Feature
Generates printable recipe cards.

## Key Functions

### generate()
Handles recipe generation process.

### buildPrompt()
Creates AI prompt.

### callGroq()
Sends API request.

### renderRecipe()
Displays recipe.

### copyRecipe()
Copies recipe text.

## Testing

### Functional Testing
All features tested successfully.

### API Testing
Verified AI communication.

### UI Testing
Responsive on desktop and mobile.

### Error Handling
Handled invalid API responses.


# Phase 4 – Results, Conclusion & Future Scope

## Results

Successfully developed an AI-powered recipe generator that creates recipes instantly based on user requirements.

## Advantages

- Saves time
- Personalized recipes
- Reduces food waste
- User-friendly design
- Fast AI responses

## Limitations

- Internet required
- Depends on API availability
- No user account system

